quran[16]{c,v,t}:
  7,105,"“It is obligatory for me not to speak concerning Allah except the truth; I have come to you all with a clear sign from your Lord, therefore let the Descendants of Israel go with me.”"
  7,106,"Said Firaun, “If you have come with a sign, then present it if you are truthful!”"
  7,107,"Therefore Moosa put down his staff – it immediately turned into a visible python."
  7,108,"And putting his hand in his bosom, withdrew it – so it shone brightly before the beholders."
  7,109,"Said the chieftains of Firaun’s people, “He is really an expert magician.”"
  7,110,"“He wishes to expel you all from your kingdom; so what do you advise?”"
  7,111,"They said, “Stop him and his brother, and send announcers to the cities to gather people.”"
  7,112,"“To bring all the expert magicians to you.”"
  7,113,"And the magicians came to Firaun, and said, “Will we get some reward if we are victorious?”"
  7,114,"He said, “Yes, and you will then become close to me.”"
  7,115,"They said, “O Moosa! You may throw first – or shall we be the first to throw?”"
  7,116,"He said, “You throw”; when they threw, they cast a magic spell upon the people’s eyes and terrified them, and they brought a great magic."
  7,117,"And We inspired Moosa that, “Put forth your staff”; it immediately began swallowing up their fabrications."
  7,118,"So the truth was proved and their works were disproved."
  7,119,"They were therefore defeated here and they turned back humiliated."
  7,120,"And the magicians were obliged to fall prostrate."
